CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 19, 1952, pg. 2, reads: "Dempster Dumpster - The first of the 'Dempster Dumpsters' which the City of Pittsburgh has purchased at a cost of $25,000 in hope that citizens who now illegally dump refuse on 'hokey piles' will use them, was demonstrated here Tuesday afternoon at the corner of Bryn Mawr Road and Ossipee Street. In the photo are Public Works Director James S. Devlin and Bureau Refuse Superintendent James J. Hughes. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: James S. Devlin and James J. Hughes viewing City of Pittsburgh Dempster Dumpster truck lifting Dumpster, at corner of Bryn Mawr Road and Ossipee Street, Hill District
